"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427583","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<p>Since 2003 the Middlesex North West London Army Cadet Force have returned L86A1-SA-80 light support weapons to Ministry of Defence Donnington on one occasion. Four L86 A1-SA-80 weapons were returned in January 2011.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-11-16T17:06:34.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427583/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427583/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427583/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-10","MOD Donnington","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many L86A1-SA-80 light support weapons have been returned from the Middlesex North West London Army cadet force to his Department's Donnington barracks since 2003.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","15703"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427584","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-17","<p>The document referred to by the hon. Member is available in redacted version over the internet. This Department has no record of receiving a copy from the United States administration.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-11-17T15:17:16.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427584/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427584/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427584/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-10","USSR: Intelligence Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the Government has been provided with a copy of the US President's Foreign Intelligence Advisory Board report of 15 February 1990, entitled The Soviet 'War Scare', by the US administration.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","15747"
