"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427709","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-17","<p>I refer my hon. Friend to the answer I gave on 19 November 2015 to Question UIN <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=14200" target="_blank">14200</a>.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-11-17T11:53:01.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427709/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427709/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427709/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-10","Eyesight: Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what proportion of medical research spending is directed toward eye disease.","false","Biography information for Derek Thomas","St Ives","Derek Thomas","15919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427710","Department of Health","false","2015-11-19","<p>From the data collected it is not possible to identify how much was spent specifically on treating patients with age-related macular degeneration.</p><br /><p>No estimate has been made of the annual cost of treating age related macular degeneration by 2050.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","15918","2015-11-19T17:50:12.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427710/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427710/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427710/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-10","Macular Degeneration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the likely annual cost to the NHS of treating age-related macular degeneration by 2050.","false","Biography information for Derek Thomas","St Ives","Derek Thomas","15920"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427711","Department of Health","false","2015-11-17","<p>Our comprehensive childhood obesity strategy, due to be published in the new year, will be looking at areas for potential action including diet and sugar consumption which are risk factors in poor oral health and tooth decay.</p><br /><p>The Department is working with NHS England to test a possible new dental contract which will increase access and improve oral health. Building on earlier pilots we are about to move to a new stage of testing by establishing prototypes. The new dental prototypes will continue to test a clinical care pathway focussed on preventing future dental disease. This approach includes offering patients personalised care plans and advice to both patients and parents on diet and good oral hygiene.</p><br /><p>In 2014 Public Health England (PHE) published an evidence informed toolkit for local authorities to support their work on oral health improvement among children and young people. PHE also published an evidence based toolkit for dental teams to support preventive advice and treatment for their patients. These toolkits include oral health improvement programmes and advice focussing on a healthier diet and reducing the consumption of free sugars.</p><br /><p>In addition these toolkits include other methods to improve oral health, for example tooth brushing programmes and fluoride varnish application.</p><br /><p>The PHE report <em>Local authorities improving oral health: commissioning better oral health for children and young people: An evidence-informed toolkit for local authorities</em> is attached and can be found at:</p><br /><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/321503/CBOHMaindocumentJUNE2014.pdf" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/321503/CBOHMaindocumentJUNE2014.pdf</a></p><br /><p>The PHE report <em>Delivering better oral health: an evidence-based toolkit for prevention</em> is attached and can be found at:</p><br /><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/367563/DBOHv32014OCTMainDocument_3.pdf" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/367563/DBOHv32014OCTMainDocument_3.pdf</a></p><br />","Battersea","Jane Ellison","15910","2015-11-17T16:13:25.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427711/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427711/answer","Local authorities improving oral health.pdf ; Delivering better oral health.pdf","Local authorities improving oral health.pdf ; Delivering better oral health.pdf","Improving oral health ; Delivering better oral health","Improving oral health ; Delivering better oral health","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427711/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-10","Obesity: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to improve oral health as part of the childhood obesity strategy.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","15909"
