"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426964","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-17","<p>The UK’s trade in goods deficit with the EU was £78.9bn in 2014. The overall trade in goods and services deficit with the EU was £61.7bn.</p><p>The UK’s total trade deficit is financed by a net inflow of investment in the financial account, for which data is not available on a geographical basis. The UK’s financial account surplus was £89.4bn in 2014.</p><p>Source: ONS Pink Book 2015</p>",,"Lord Maude of Horsham",,"2015-11-17T17:52:40.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426964/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426964/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426964/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-09","UK Trade with EU","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what was the deficit in trade with the EU in 2014 in (1) goods, and (2) overall in goods and services; and how that deficit is financed.","false","Biography information for Lord Stoddart of Swindon",,"Lord Stoddart of Swindon","HL3451"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426965","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-23","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis.</p>",,"Lord Maude of Horsham",,"2015-11-23T17:40:11.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426965/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426965/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426965/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-09","UK Membership of EU","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their assessment of (1) the recent report by former UK ambassadors to the EU that, if the UK left the EU, access to free-trade deals would be lost with 51 states; (2) whether those states would, as a consequence, lose free access to the UK market; and (3) the overall effect on the UK's trading balance of those assessments.","false","Biography information for Lord Stoddart of Swindon",,"Lord Stoddart of Swindon","HL3452"
